comments.body:
@SteveL-MSFT the original cmdlet example was out-dated and removed in #3409, which added a new documentation about hosting powershell core in .NET Core applications.

To create a .NET Core cmdlet, you just need to reference the NuGet package `System.Management.Automation` from the [`powershell-core`](https://powershell.myget.org/gallery/powershell-core) feed. It's the same as how you use any other NuGet packages.

So it seems to me that nothing needs to be done. Can we close this issue?
